   *INITIAL
   *************************************************************************
   ** Initial Conditions Section
   *************************************************************************
   *USER_INPUT                     ** This keyword replaces VERTICAL *OFF              
   *PRES *KVAR                     ** Pressure is constant in each layer 
     4000.0   3990.3   3984.3      ** but varies between the layers.
   *PB   *CON                      ** Initial bubble point pressure is
     2302.3                        ** constant throughout
   *PBS  *CON                      ** Initial solvent bubble point pressure
     2302.3                        ** is constant throughout.
   *SW  *CON                       ** Water saturations are constant.
     0.20
   *SO  *CON                       ** Oil saturations are constant.
     0.80
                               

   *NUMERICAL
   *************************************************************************
   ** Numerical Methods Control Section
   *************************************************************************
   *DTMAX 100.
   *MAXSTEPS  999                  ** Maximum number of time steps
   *NORM *PRESS  500.0             ** Normal maximum changes per time step
   *AIM *THRESH  .25  .25   


   *RUN
   *************************************************************************
   ** Well Data Section
   *************************************************************************
   *DATE  1986 12 1
   *DTWELL 1.000   

   ** Two injectors are defined for the same grid block, to model one
   ** injection well in the problem. This is to allow easy switching
   ** between water injection and solvent injection during the WAG
   ** process without having to completely redefine the injector.
   ** At least one of the injectors is shutin at all times.   

   *WELL 1 'Water Injector'      ** Water Injector               
   *WELL 2 'Producer'              
   *WELL 3 'Solvent Injector'    ** Solvent Injector   

   ** All wells have the same geometry.
   **            rad   geofac  wfrac  skin
   *GEOMETRY *K  0.25   0.34    1.0    0.0   

   ** For the first two years both injectors are shut in;
   ** only the producer is operational.   

   *INJECTOR *MOBWEIGHT 1
   *INCOMP  *WATER            
   *OPERATE *MAX *STW   12000.0
   *OPERATE *MAX *BHP   10000.0
   *PERF *GEO 1      
   ** if  jf  kf  ff 
       1   1   3   1.0
   *SHUTIN 1   

   *PRODUCER 2
   *OPERATE *MAX *STO 12000.0      ** Primary operating constraint.
   *OPERATE *MIN *BHP  1000.0      ** Bottomhole pressure is also monitored.
   *MONITOR *GOR    10000.0  *STOP ** Monitor GOR and stop simulation if hit.
   *MONITOR *WCUT 0.8330002  *STOP ** Monitor Water Cut and stop simulation.
   *PERF *GEO 2      
   ** if  jf  kf  ff 
       7   7   1   1.0    

   *INJECTOR *MOBWEIGHT 3
   *INCOMP   *SOLVENT
   *OPERATE *MAX *STS   1.2E+7
   *OPERATE *MAX *BHP   10000.0
   *PERF *GEO 3      
   ** if  jf  kf  ff 
       1   1   3   1.0
   *SHUTIN 3   

   *AIMSET *CON 0
   *AIMWELL *WELLN
        
   *TIME  365.000                  ** Forces time step to end at one year.   

   *TIME  730.000                  ** Forces time step to end at two years.
   *OPEN 1                         ** Open water injector, begin WAG process.
   *AIMSET *CON 0                  ** Reset all blocks to explicit.
   *AIMWELL *WELLN                 ** Set well blocks and neighbours implicit.   

   *TIME 1095.0
   *SHUTIN 1                       ** Shutin water injector.
   *OPEN 3                         ** Open solvent injector.
   *AIMSET *CON 0
   *AIMWELL *WELLN

